10:
Comiiing!
Oh, this truly is a lovely forest, Alk. So 
full of life and beauty...
13:
I thought you'd like it.
You know, all this was raised by 
Regitare.
16: Regitare? What kind of person is he?
20:
I, uh... don't know if I'd call him 
a person...
26:
The undead! How dare you step foot 
into this forest?!
34:
I was wondering what all the ruckus 
was about. Should've known it'd be 
you, Alk.
40:
Regitare! I'm really sorry about this! I'll 
clear up this misunderstanding right 
away!
51:
I'm so very sorry... I was certain you 
were a monster, come to lay waste to 
the forest.
56:
Ehh, don't worry about it, lass. 
Anyone'd think that, after clapping 
eyes on these rattlebones.
60:
For sure. Remember the first time Light 
met you? Challenged you to battle as 
the King of the Dead.
64:
Did he now? Must've slipped the old 
skull!
68:
A forest of life... raised by the dead. 
What a topsy-turvy place.
72:
Oh, it's pure chaos here.
Hey, Regitare. Tell her about all the 
monsters lurking around.
88:
Y-yeah, I'm fine.
How about you, Regitare?
102:
I really was right to leave home. If 
I hadn't, I would've never experienced 
any of this!
107:
Speaking of home, you're an elf, aren't 
you, lass?
109:
Mind telling an old bag of bones about 
your enchanted forest?
114:
I'd be delighted to! We've all the time 
in the world, after all.
